Attach
------

^B          macro                  call urlview to extract URLs out of a message
^E          edit-type              edit attachment content type
^F          forget-passphrase      wipe passphrase(s) from memory
<Enter>     view-attach            view attachment using mailcap entry if
                                   necessary
^K          extract-keys           extract supported public keys
<Return>    view-attach            view attachment using mailcap entry if
                                   necessary
<Esc>P      check-traditional-pgp  check for classic PGP
<Esc>e      resend-message         use the current message as a template for a
                                   new one
L           list-reply             reply to specified mailing list
T           view-text              view attachment as text
b           bounce-message         remail a message to another user
d           delete-entry           delete the current entry
f           forward-message        forward a message with comments
g           group-reply            reply to all recipients
h           display-toggle-weed    display message and toggle header weeding
m           view-mailcap           force viewing of attachment using mailcap
p           print-entry            print the current entry
r           reply                  reply to a message
s           save-entry             save message/attachment to a mailbox/file
u           undelete-entry         undelete the current entry
v           collapse-parts         toggle display of subparts
|           pipe-entry             pipe message/attachment to a shell command

Compose
-------

^B          M <enter-command> s... call urlview to extract URLs out of a message
^D          toggle-disposition     toggle disposition between inline/attachment
^E          edit-encoding          edit attachment transfer-encoding
^F          forget-passphrase      wipe passphrase(s) from memory
<Enter>     view-attach            view attachment using mailcap entry if
                                   necessary
<Return>    view-attach            view attachment using mailcap entry if
                                   necessary
^O          rename-attachment      send attachment with a different name
^T          edit-type              edit attachment content type
^Xe         edit-file              edit the file to be attached
<Esc>f      edit-from              edit the from field
<Esc>k      attach-key             attach a PGP public key
A           attach-message         attach message(s) to this message
C           copy-file              save message/attachment to a mailbox/file
D           detach-file            delete the current entry
E           edit-headers           edit the message with headers
F           filter-entry           filter attachment through a shell command
G           get-attachment         get a temporary copy of an attachment
P           postpone-message       save this message to send later
R           rename-file            rename/move an attached file
S           smime-menu             show S/MIME options
T           tag-entry              tag the current entry
U           update-encoding        update an attachment's encoding info
a           attach-file            attach file(s) to this message
b           edit-bcc               edit the BCC list
c           edit-cc                edit the CC list
d           edit-description       edit attachment description
e           edit-message           edit the message
f           edit-fcc               enter a file to save a copy of this message
                                   in
h           display-toggle-weed    display message and toggle header weeding
i           ispell                 run ispell on the message
l           print-entry            print the current entry
m           edit-mime              edit attachment using mailcap entry
n           new-mime               compose new attachment using mailcap entry
p           pgp-menu               show PGP options
r           edit-reply-to          edit the Reply-To field
s           edit-subject           edit the subject of this message
t           edit-to                edit the TO list
u           toggle-unlink          toggle whether to delete file after sending
                                   it
w           write-fcc              write the message to a folder
y           send-message           send the message
|           pipe-entry             pipe message/attachment to a shell command
<F5>        M :source '/home/da... send mail via ssh
<F6>        M :source '/home/da... Mailboxes from offlineimap

Unbound:
attach-news-message                attach news article(s) to this message
edit-newsgroups                    edit the newsgroups list
edit-followup-to                   edit the Followup-To field
edit-x-comment-to                  edit the X-Comment-To field
toggle-recode                      toggle recoding of this attachment

Browser
-------

<Tab>       toggle-mailboxes       toggle whether to browse mailboxes or all
                                   files
<Space>     view-file              view file
.           buffy-list             list mailboxes with new mail
=           goto-folder            swap the current folder position with $folder
                                   if it exists
@           display-filename       display the currently selected file's name
C           create-mailbox         create a new mailbox (IMAP only)
N           select-new             select a new file in this directory
O           sort-reverse           sort messages in reverse order
T           toggle-subscribed      toggle view all/subscribed mailboxes (IMAP
                                   only)
c           change-dir             change directories
d           delete-mailbox         delete the current mailbox (IMAP only)
m           enter-mask             enter a file mask
o           sort                   sort messages
r           rename-mailbox         rename the current mailbox (IMAP only)
s           subscribe              subscribe to current mbox (IMAP/NNTP only)
u           unsubscribe            unsubscribe from current mbox (IMAP/NNTP only)
y           exit                   exit this menu

unbound:
check-new                          check mailboxes for new mail
reload-active                      load list of all newsgroups from NNTP server
subscribe-pattern                  subscribe to newsgroups matching a pattern
unsubscribe-pattern                unsubscribe from newsgroups matching a
                                   pattern
catchup                            mark all articles in newsgroup as read
uncatchup                          mark all articles in newsgroup as unread

Query
-----

A           query-append           append new query results to current results
Q           query                  query external program for addresses
a           create-alias           create an alias from a message sender
m           mail                   compose a new mail message

Alias
-----

<Enter>     select-entry           select the current entry
<Return>    select-entry           select the current entry
<Space>     tag-entry              tag the current entry
d           delete-entry           delete the current entry
u           undelete-entry         undelete the current entry

Pgp Menu
--------

%           view-name              view the key's user id
c           verify-key             verify a PGP public key

Postpone Menu
-------------

d           delete-entry           delete the current entry
u           undelete-entry         undelete the current entry
My bindings
===========

Generic
--------

macro generic,pager <f2> "!less $HOME/.mutt/doc/pattern\n" "Mutt Pattern"

bind generic,pager j   next-entry
bind generic,pager k   previous-entry
bind generic,index,pager \Cb previous-page
bind generic,index,pager \Cf next-page
bind generic       ,H  current-top
bind generic       ,L  current-bottom
bind generic       ,M  current-middle
bind generic,index,pager \Cn next-line
bind generic,index,pager \Cp previous-line
bind generic,index 0   first-entry
bind generic,index G   last-entry
bind generic,index ,G  first-entry
bind generic,pager <esc>n search-opposite
bind generic       ,q exit

Index
------

macro index,pager \cu |urlview\n 'call urlview to extract URLs out of a message'
macro generic,index,pager \ca "<shell-escape>abook<return>" "launch abook"
macro index,pager A "<pipe-message>abook --add-email<return>" "add the sender address to abook"
macro index,pager,browser ,mi ":source '$HOME/.mutt/config.rb imap |'\n" "Imap Accounts"
macro index,pager,browser ,mI ":unmailboxes imap://* \n" "Clear imap mailboxes"
macro index,pager,browser ,mo ":source '$HOME/.mutt/config.rb mailboxes offlineimap |'\n" "Mailboxes from offlineimap"
macro index,pager,browser ,mC ":unmailboxes * \n" "Clear all mailboxes"
bind index,pager ,ml imap-logout-all
macro index,pager,compose ,ls ":source '$HOME/.mutt/config.rb smtp ssh |'\n" "send mail via ssh"
macro index,pager,compose ,lm ":source '$HOME/.mutt/config.rb smtp |" "select smtp"

bind index,pager x  change-vfolder
bind index,pager ,x vfolder-from-query
macro index,pager \Cx ":source '$HOME/.mutt/config.rb mailboxes virtual |\n:set sidebar_visible\n<sidebar-toggle-virtual>" "Toggle the sidebar into virtual folders"
macro index,pager,browser ,mv ":source '$HOME/.mutt/config.rb mailboxes virtual |'\n" "Add virtual mailboxes"
macro index,pager,browser ,mV ":unvirtual-mailboxes * \n" "Clear virtual mailboxes"
macro index,pager X "<change-vfolder>?" "List virtual mailboxes"
bind browser X exit
bind index ,< vfolder-window-backward
bind index ,> vfolder-window-forward
bind index,pager ,lt entire-thread

bind index       +   collapse-thread
bind index       -   collapse-thread
bind index       *   collapse-all
bind index,pager ,d  delete-subthread
bind index,pager ,D  delete-thread
bind index,pager ,n  next-subthread
bind index,pager ,N  next-thread
bind index,pager ,p  previous-subthread
bind index,pager ,P  previous-thread
bind index,pager ,r  read-subthread
bind index,pager ,R  read-thread
bind index       ,t  tag-subthread
bind index       ,T  tag-thread
bind index,pager ,u  undelete-subthread
bind index,pager ,U  undelete-thread

 # transposition of p/P bindings
bind index,pager p  parent-message
bind index,pager P  print-message
 #bind index \Ct query
bind index       ,F  fetch-mail #pop3
bind index,pager ,f  imap-fetch-mail
bind index,pager ,\cF  forget-passphrase
bind index,pager <esc>c  change-folder-readonly
bind index,pager ,c  next-unread-mailbox
 # e is edit-or-view-raw-message
bind index,pager ,e  resend-message
bind index,pager E   compose-to-sender
bind index,pager ,@  compose-to-sender
bind index,pager ,k  mail-key
bind index       ,sl show-limit
bind index       ,sv show-version
bind index       ,L  limit-current-thread
bind index,pager ,v  view-raw-message
bind index,pager ,Y  modify-labels
bind index,pager ,z  mail-key
bind index,pager ,Z  extract-keys

 # decode/decrypt-save is <Esc>s/<esc>C
bind index,pager ,S  decrypt-save
bind index,pager ,C  decrypt-copy

bind index,pager ,<TAB> previous-new-then-unread
bind index,pager ,j   next-unread
bind index,pager ,k   previous-unread
bind index,pager ,J   next-thread
bind index,pager ,K   previous-thread
bind index,pager J   next-undeleted
bind index,pager K   previous-undeleted
bind index <right>  next-unread
bind index <left>   previous-unread
bind index ,<right> next-new-then-unread
bind index ,<left>  previous-new-then-unread
bind index ,<up>    parent-message
bind index ,<down>  root-message

Pager
-----
bind pager <Up>    previous-line
bind pager <Down>  next-line
bind pager K       previous-line
bind pager J       next-line
macro pager <pagedown> ":set pager_stop\n<next-page>:unset pager_stop\n" "next-page"

